It was urged in his behalf, that it was the intereſt of the Commonwealth, to expel Archelaus out of Egypt; whoſe Fleet hinder'd the Navigation and Commerce of Rome, and the adjacent Seas, and gave all ſorts of aſſiſtance to Pyrats, who exerciſed all manner of Cruelties upon the Subjects of the Republick. It was alſo alleadged, this expedition was permitted unto Gabinius, by a Law whereof we have no Record;

that at the worſt, the Oracle did not relate the preſent buſineſs, and that the matter hapned long before, in the Perſon of a former King of Egypt, whereof I made mention, who had alſo been expell'd out of his Kingdom, and pray'd aſſiſtance of the Senat. But if the Oracle meant his Succeſſour,
Dion. l. 39. Ad Att. l. 4. Ep. 16. l. 3. Ep. 4. the Sybil not having expreſs'd what Puniſhment they deſerv'd, that ſhould reſtore this Prince, by force of Arms againſt its Prohibition, no body hath right to determin it.
